{"000-section": {"000-title": "Rajasthan Menstrual Hygiene Scheme (MHS) \u2013 Sanitary Napkins for Women"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Rajasthan Menstrual Hygiene Scheme (MHS) for Women", "001-normal": "The important features and highlights of this MHS Scheme are as follows:-", "002-listElement": "- Approx. 1.2 crore women in the age group of 15 to 45 years can take benefits of this Health Scheme.", "003-listElement": "- The state govt. has allocated Rs. 76 crore for Menstrual Hygiene Scheme (MHS). Govt. will distribute sanitary napkins and spread hygiene message among women.", "004-listElement": "- As per Nation Family Health Survey report (2015-16), only 55% women (15-45 years) are using hygiene protection methods during their menstrual periods.", "005-listElement": "- In urban areas, situation is slightly better in comparison to rural areas. Around 78% of women in urban areas and 50% of women in rural areas uses sanitary napkins, locally prepared pads and tampons as hygiene methods.", "006-listElement": "- As per the Survey reports, 45% women between 15 to 24 years in the state are at higher risk of getting exposed to menstrual hygiene related diseases.", "007-listElement": "- Such women can be exposed to fungal infection, urinary tract infection, reproductive tract infection and other health diseases."}}